      • Content

        public Content(int id)
        Creates an instance of the Content type specified by its ID. If id is 0, the default Content is created. If id is smaller than 0 or if an internal error occurs, then an empty Content is created.
        Parameters:
        id - the Content type ID

      • Content

    • Method Detail

      • merge

        public Content merge(Content content)
        Merges another content into this one. - The properties of the provided content are copied into the current content - The compatibility is adjusted to include all compatibilities of the provided content - The text format of the provided content is appended to the current with a "\n" separator - The html format of the provided content is appended to the current with a "
        " separator - The uuid and timestamp of the current content are preserved - Properties common to both will be overwritten by the provided content's
        Parameters:
        content - the content to merge into this one
        Returns:
        the merged current content
